author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump told reporters that he had been informed that a hostage and ceasefire deal is “very close” as Secretary of State Marco Rubio handed him a handwritten note during a roundtable event at the White House.
title: Rubio interrupts Trump's roundtable to hand him note about Gaza deal

author: CNN
description: CNN's Pamela Brown speaks with Chicago mayor Brandon Johnson after President Donald Trump called for Johnson and Illinois Governor JB Pritzker to be jailed for "failing to protect" ICE officers. #CNN #News
title: 'I'm not going anywhere': Chicago mayor responds to Trump's call for him to be jailed

author: CNN
description:
Country music legend Dolly Parton took to social media to “put everybody’s mind at ease” following rumors about her health.

#CNN #News
title: Dolly Parton to fans: ‘I’m not dying’

author: CNN
description: In an interview with CNN's Dana Bash, Speaker Emerita Nancy Pelosi criticizes President Trump over former FBI director James Comey's criminal indictment for allegedly lying to Congress in 2020 about leaks.
title: Nancy Pelosi reveals why she ripped up copy of Trump's speech in 2020

author: CNN
description: Former House Speaker Rep. Nancy Pelosi (D-CA) sat down with CNN's Dana Bash for a wide-ranging interview. #CNN #News
title: One-on-one with former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi

author: CNN
description: Eighty years after the Japanese surrendered, formally ending World War II, CNN’s Stephanie Elam sat down with US Navy veteran Doyle Boothroy, who served on the USS Missouri during the war. Boothroy says he first boarded the Missouri in February of 1945 when he was 19 years old. He recalls what life was like on the “Mighty Mo,” sailing close to a typhoon and watching as members of the Japanese Imperial Government boarded the Missouri on September 2, 1945, to take part in the surrender ceremony.  #CNN #News
title: Veteran reflects on World War II that ended 80 years ago

author: CNN
description: Former FBI Director James Comey is caught in the middle of President Donald Trump’s second-term retribution campaign. CNN’s Marshall Cohen explains how Comey wasn’t always at the top of Trump’s enemies list. #cnn #news
title: Breaking down Trump and Comey's long history

author: CNN
description: TV host and painter Bob Ross has 30 original paintings going up for auction. All profits will go to US public TV and radio stations. This comes after Congress cut funding in support of public broadcasting.
title: How Bob Ross could save your public TV station

author: CNN
description:
Nine months after the Palisades Fire, which claimed the lives of a dozen people and burned down thousands of homes and businesses in Southern California, officials have arrested a suspect in Florida on suspicion of arson. Jonathan Rinderknecht, 29, is facing a federal charge of destruction of property by means of fire, according to Bill Essayli, the acting US attorney for Southern California.

CNN security correspondent Josh Campbell reports from Los Angeles. #CNN #News
title: Arson suspect charged in connection with deadly Palisades Fire in Southern California

author: CNN
description: Former FBI Director James Comey pleaded not guilty to two criminal charges at his arraignment. His lawyers said in court they plan to file several motions they hope will kill the case before it makes it to a jury. CNN's Evan Perez reports. #cnn #news
title: Former FBI Director James Comey pleads not guilty

author: CNN
description: Chicago Mayor Brandon Johnson (D) responds after President Donald Trump called for Johnson and Illinois Governor JB Pritzker to be jailed for "failing to protect" ICE officers. #CNN #News
title: Chicago mayor responds to Trump's call to have him jailed

author: CNN
description: Prosecutors arrested and charged 29-year-old Jonathan Rinderknecht Florida with destruction of property by means of fire in connection to the Palisades Fire, which burned thousands of homes and killed 12 people in Los Angeles.
title: Suspect charged in connection with deadly Palisades Fire

author: CNN
description: In a video released by a Ukrainian National Guard Unit, Lasar’s Group, a Ukrainian drone appears to land and self-detonate on a Russian missile launcher. Russia has not confirmed the incident and it is not clear if there were any casualties. #cnn #news
title: Russian troops appear to run from Ukrainian drone on front line

author: CNN
description: An attack by Myanmar's ruling junta on protesters at a Buddhist festival has killed at least 20. The junta used a motorised paraglider to drop explosives on the gathering on Wednesday. A spokesperson for the junta did not respond to calls seeking comment, according to Reuters. #cnn #myanmar
title: At least 20 killed in junta attack in Myanmar

author: CNN
description:
The Federal Aviation Administration is again reporting short staffing at air traffic control operations as the government shutdown enters its eighth day.

CNN aviation correspondent Pete Muntean reports from Reagan National Airport in Virginia, and CNN's Audie Cornish speaks with Rep. Hillary Scholten (D-MI), who serves on the House Transportation and Infrastructure Committee. #CNN #News
title: Widespread airport delays amid government shutdown

author: CNN
description: CNN staffers in three cities around the world wore chemical-tracking wristbands and found exposure to dozens of potentially harmful compounds — including phthalates and bisphenols — showing just how pervasive plastics are in everyday life. #CNN #News
title: Wristbands reveal invisible toxins

author: CNN
description:
The president ramped up his criticism Wednesday of Chicago Mayor Brandon Johnson and Democratic Gov. JB Pritzker, who called the Guard callup “Trump’s invasion” over the weekend. “Chicago Mayor should be in jail for failing to protect Ice Officers! Governor Pritzker also!” Trump wrote on Truth Social.

CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Katrina Thompson, mayor of Broadview, Illinois, the Chicago suburb where an ICE facility has been drawing protests. #CNN #News
title: Trump calls for jailing Illinois governor, Chicago mayor

author: CNN
description: Four police officers were injured and 13 people were arrested during a pro-Palestinian protest in Boston on Tuesday evening, according to local police. None of the injuries were life-threatening, and all arrestees were charged with resisting arrest, disorderly conduct, and disturbing the peace.
title: Clashes at Boston protest lead to arrests and injuries

author: CNN
description: Speaking at the “Day of Unreasonable Conversation” summit, an invitation-only event for writers in Los Angeles, former vice president Kamala Harris had some harsh words on the current political moment. #CNN #News
title: Kamala Harris issues sharp words about political climate

author: CNN
description: Former FBI Director James Comey on Wednesday pleaded not guilty in Alexandria, Virginia, to charges of providing false statements and obstructing a congressional proceeding. He could face a maximum of five years in prison if convicted. CNN’s Katelyn Polantz and Evan Perez report.  #CNN #News
title: Trial date set after Comey enters not guilty plea

author: CNN
description: Football season has returned but so has a disturbing trend: fan violence. Brawls in the stands flood social media feeds. CNN’s Ed Lavandera explores the phenomenon in “Bad Sports: When Fans Get Violent,” Saturday, October 11 at 8PM ET/PT on CNN’s “The Whole Story with Anderson Cooper.”  #CNN #News
title: Viral videos put fan violence back in the spotlight

author: CNN
description: Do you use social media for news? You're not alone. CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down the numbers. #CNN #News
title: Social media as a news source: CNN's Harry Enten runs the numbers

author: CNN
description: Former First Lady Jacqueline Kennedy travelled to Cambodia in 1967, staying at the Hotel Le Royal in Phnom Penh. More than five decades later, the staff still welcome visitors, like CNN's Lilit Marcus, who are intrigued by the legacy she left there. For more on the rest of Kennedy's Cambodia visit, go to cnn.com/travel. #cnn #travel #cambodia #jackiekennedy
title: This hotel still keeps Jackie Kennedy’s cocktail glass

author: CNN
description: Sen. Richard Blumenthal (D-CT) responds to attacks by President Trump and Attorney General Pam Bondi, who claim he lied about his military service record: "It is just so completely deceptive and distorted." Sen. Blumenthal speaks with CNN's Kaitlan Collins about the Judiciary Committee hearing, the James Comey prosecution and other subjects. #CNN #News
title: Sen. Blumenthal responds to AG Bondi's attack: 'Discredited. . .distorted and deceptive'

author: CNN
description: Argentinian President Javier Milei gave a classic rock performance at a political rally for the launch of his new book. Milei also used the event to pay tribute to the victims of 2023 October 7 attack in southern Israel by Hamas, calling for the release of the remaining hostages.
title: Argentina’s president performs rock song at rally

author: CNN
description: As the government shutdown dragged on through its sixth day, Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer (D-NY) praised Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene (R-GA) for calling out Republican leadership over not having a plan to extend enhanced Obamacare subsidies.  #CNN #News
title: ‘Representative Greene said it perfectly’: Hear Schumer praise MTG’s health care stance

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins pressed Rep. Jim Jordan (R-OH) about where he stands on back pay for furloughed federal workers as the government shutdown enters its second week.  #CNN #News
title: Hear what Rep. Jim Jordan said about back pay for furloughed workers

author: CNN
description: Bad Bunny was hit by a foul ball at at a Yankees vs. Blue Jays game on Tuesday night. The moment has gone viral after the rapper picked up the ball which landed near his seat. #cnn #badbunny #yankees
title: Foul ball lands on Bad Bunny at Yankees game

author: CNN
description: In a September press conference in front of Capitol Hill a victim of Jeffrey Epstein said that survivors were talking about creating their own "client list." CNN spoke with numerous Epstein survivors, lawyers representing dozens of victims and congressional staff familiar with Epstein-related investigations on Capitol Hill — they warned that such an effort would put Epstein's victims in greater danger. CNN's MJ Lee reports. #CNN #News
title: Some Epstein survivors see danger in creating a 'client list'

author: CNN
description: Attorney General Pam Bondi's appearance before the Senate Judiciary Committee was filled with stonewalling and attacks against the senators asking her questions. CNN Senior Commentator Ana Navarro remembers Bondi from earlier in her career in Florida and finds her unrecognizable now. #CNN #News
title: Ana Navarro: Will the real Pam Bondi please stand up?

author: CNN
description: More aid ships that are part of an organization called the Freedom Flotilla Coalition were intercepted on Wednesday by Israeli forces as it was roughly 120 nautical miles from Gaza, according to the organizers. This comes after Israel detained dozens of activists on the Global Sumud Flotilla last week, including Greta Thunberg. #CNN #news
title: Israeli forces intercept more Gaza-bound aid ships

author: CNN
description: Bad Bunny caught a foul ball at at a Yankees vs. Blue Jays game on Tuesday night. The moment has gone viral after the rapper picked up the ball which landed near his seat. #cnn #badbunny #yankees #bluejays
title: Bad Bunny catches foul ball at Yankees game

author: CNN
description: Iris Stalzer, elected mayor of the town of Herdecke in western Germany last month, was found with life-threatening injuries from a stabbing attack. Stalzer’s health “remains in danger,” according to police. #cnn #news #germany
title: Newly-elected German mayor stabbed outside home

author: CNN
description: Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem met with Portland Mayor Keith Wilson during her Tuesday trip to Oregon’s biggest city. Noem said she threatened the mayor during the meeting to send “four times the amount of federal officers” to Portland if he doesn’t follow through on security measures for government officers. #cnn #news #politics
title: Secretary Noem met with Portland mayor during tense Oregon visit

author: CNN
description: The Super Dry, an iconic product by Japan’s largest beer maker Asahi, is running low. CNN’s Hanako Montgomery explains why. #CNN #News #Japan
title: This beer could run dry in Japan. Why?

author: CNN
description: New York City Democratic mayoral nominee Zohran Mamdani reflected on the second anniversary of the October 7 attacks Tuesday, issuing a statement in memory of Israeli victims and hostages still held by Hamas but also critical of the US and Israeli governments. CNN's Gloria Pazmino reports. #cnn, #news, #politics
title: Mamdani reflects on October 7 attacks

author: CNN
description: The government shutdown is having major impacts on air traffic control capabilities at some of the nation's busiest airports. CNN's Pete Muntean has the latest.
title: Delays spread to major airports amid shutdown

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump on Tuesday compared Democrats to “insurrectionists” when describing the passage of his “big, beautiful bill” over the summer. #CNN #News
title: Trump compares democrats to 'insurrectionists' as government shutdown continues

author: CNN
description: Grammy award-winning country singer Zach Bryan is speaking out after the internet has reacted to Bryan seemingly taking a swipe at ICE raids in a new song.
title: Country star Zach Bryan takes swipe at ICE in new song

author: CNN
description: Members of the Texas National Guard, mobilized by Trump, have arrived at a military facility near Chicago for legal and crowd control training ahead of any specific assignments, a law enforcement source says. #CNN #News
title: Troops arrive in Illinois for training amid Trump push to deploy guard

author: CNN
description: Five suspects have been arrested after what officials describe as an assassination attempt on Ecuadorian President Daniel Noboa. Energy minister Ines Manzano says the president’s convoy was attacked by a crowd of roughly 500 people throwing rocks while he was en route to announce new infrastructure projects.
title: Mob attacks motorcade of Ecuador's president

author: CNN
description: CNN's Erin Burnett speaks to former federal prosecutor Ryan Crosswell, who resigned after the Department of Justice decided to drop corruption case charges against New York City Mayor Eric Adams. #CNN #News
title: DOJ attorney who resigned speaks out as Bondi evades questions

author: CNN
description: CNN's Priscilla Alvarez talks with El Centro Border Patrol Sector Chief Gregory Bovino about why his agency uses aggressive tactics in places like Los Angeles and Chicago.
title: CNN asks border patrol official about aggressive tactics. Hear his response
